      <section eId="sec_178_05">
        <num>178.05</num>
        <heading>Criminal diversion of prescription medications and prescriptions; limitation</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_178_05__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a duly licensed physician or other person authorized to issue a\nprescription acting in good faith in the lawful course of his or her\nprofession; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_178_05__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a duly licensed pharmacist acting in good faith in the lawful\ncourse of the practice of pharmacy; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_178_05__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a person acting in good faith seeking treatment for a medical\ncondition or assisting another person to obtain treatment for a medical\ncondition.\n  2. No provision of this article relating to the sale of a prescription\nmedication or device shall be deemed to authorize any act prohibited by\narticle thirty-three of the public health law or article two hundred\ntwenty of this chapter.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
